title: Lava Cantina - Green Dazed
content:
Green Day Summer Camp Show!

Kids are awesome, and today will be a fun day for all. Come out and support the next generation of rockers!! This unique summer camp is set up for kids ages 10-18, and it focuses on classic songs from one of the latest and greatest American punk bands, Green Day! The students work all week learning songs from Green Day's discography to prepare for their big show on July 28th at Lava Cantina. To top it off, they'll be the opening band for Green Dazed, an awesome DFW-based Green Day cover band! Come watch both bands play at no charge and enjoy some delicious food and drinks.

title: The Iron Horse Pub - Green Dazed
Fat Daddy's (Mansfield) - Green Dazed
content:
Our first time to rock out at this location, with our buds from Fool Fighters (tribute to the Foo Fighters) and Kreed (tribute to Creed).
Doors open at 8, show at 9
Ticket prices $10 after 8pm
A nice write-up:
Green Dazed is the award-winning original Texas-based Green Day tribute with the look, sound, and feel of the real thing. With an unmatched musicality, the band features experienced musicians from across the U.S. who joined forces to create an audience-interactive, high-energy tribute performance unlike any other.
Kreed is hell-bent on bringing you the most authentic Creed show outside of the band themselves. Get ready to be mesmerized!
The Fool Fighters came on to the Dallas music scene as a Foo Fighters tribute band a few years ago. Always putting out the best Foo Fighters music.

title: Trees - Green Dazed
content:
Dookie 25th Year Anniversary
On March 3, 1994 the band Green Day played on their Dookie tour at Trees in Deep Ellum in Dallas, TX.
Little known at the time and just breaking huge, they've since moved on to arenas and been a pillar in the rock / punk live music world for decades.
We carry the torch with honor and play the same venue 25 years later almost to the day.
Come. Witness history. Trees is the crown jewel of Deep Ellum.

title: Green Dazed - The Green Day Tribute Band
content:
Our tribute to Green Day keeps getting larger, come on out an see why!
We're joining forces with our friends Sedated - Ramones tribute down in historic Deep Ellum (Dallas).
$10 cover see link to tickets
Folks, this is as Dallas as it gets, if you play live music you play Deep Ellum. Period.
Catch future shows at the web page: https://www.facebook.com/greendazed/

title: Solo Acoustic Show, Mark Moss
content:
I'm back, great venue, hosts unique food selections, cocktails and of course live music.
Music starts around 8pm, right outside the venue weather permitting. Venue has inside / outside seating and bars
From their website: whitehallexchange.com
Located in the heart of the Bishop Arts District, Whitehall Exchange is truly your neighborhood connection. We offer the finest wines, liquor, cocktails, and beer as well as some of the best food in the area. Our comfortable and inviting atmosphere is perfect for the after work wind down or for a night out on the town with friends.

title: Green Dazed - The Green Day Tribute Band
content:
I joined a tribute band here in the Dallas area because tribute bands are a big deal here and Green Day music is a blast!
This is our debut show at O'Riley's in Dallas and plan on witnessing high energy, precision and showmanship. This is not your ordinary show... 3 bands performing but we're kicking things off. Cover charge is $10 starting at 7pm.
